This paper discusses a method for efficient exploration in Hierarchical Reinforcement Learning (HRL) using intrinsic motivation learning. The paper also introduces a model-free subgoal discovery method based on unsupervised learning. These topics are closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
